Prompt 2: Mannerism – Emotional Intensity 

Inspired by: The Last Judgment, Deposition from the Cross, Laocoön 

Create a Late Renaissance (Mannerist) painting (c. 1520–1600) using oil or fresco. Show elongated, twisted figures in crowded, unclear space with diagonal movement. Use unnatural colors and dramatic lighting to create tension. The composition is unbalanced and emotionally intense. 
Purpose: to express religious anxiety and instability, rejecting the calm harmony of the High Renaissance. 
